Hi; i am new to this <u>group</u>

#TwistedTuesday

After dropping my childoo at school I visit the temple. I have been doing this for the last 7 years now, even though i am not a temple person :) (that's a different story). And today while doing my parikrama (chakkar) i stubbed my pinky toe into the corner pillar made of stone :(

It's swollen as u can see and i can barely walk.

My twisted logic for this is my aunty who passed away last tuesday dinged me 'coz while looking for agarbattis for her prayer meeting, i accidentally dropped her pooja chopda (book). Her daughter, my bff immediately jokingly said in gujarati - mummy ka chopda giraya? Ab dekhna mummy kya karti hai....

I am sure aunty maroed a big ding to me!

May her soul RIP - we had many fun times and she's capable of doing that to me ;)

Any crazy unexplained things happening at ur end? Share ur twisted tales with me or post a selfie/footfie to make me feel better ;) Ouch!
